===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Coppock had a population of 36. The median age was 33.0 years. 25.0% of residents were under the age of 18 and 16.7% were 65 years of age or older. For every 100 females, there were 157.1 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 125.0 males age 18 and over. The gender makeup of the city was 61.1% male and 38.9% female.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A16140&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A16140&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A16140&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

There were 10 households and 9 families in Coppock. Of the households, 60.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 60.0% were [[Marriage|married-couple]] households, 0.0% were cohabitating-couple households, 20.0% had a male householder with no spouse or partner present, and 20.0% had a female householder with no spouse or partner present. About 10.0% were non-family households, 10.0% were made up of individuals, and 0.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

There were 18 housing units, of which 44.4% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 16.7%. The population density was 156.0 inhabitants per square mile (60.2/km<sup>2</sup>), and the housing unit density was 78.0 per square mile (30.1/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Age distribution was 27.8% under age 20, 2.8% from 20 to 24, 33.3% from 25 to 44, 19.4% from 45 to 64, and 16.7% age 65 or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

